Document: StyleBoxFlat
Path: godot/classes/class_styleboxflat.rst
Summary: StyleBoxFlat allows creating various UI looks without textures, supporting features like rounded borders, antialiasing, shadows, and skew, with a special relative system for overlapping corner radii.

By configuring various properties of this style box, you can achieve many common looks without the need of a texture. This includes optionally rounded borders, antialiasing, shadows, and skew.

Setting corner radius to high values is allowed. As soon as corners overlap, the stylebox will switch to a relative system. For example, if height = 30, corner_radius_top_left = 50, and corner_radius_bottom_left = 100, the relative system would take the 1:2 ratio of the two left corners to calculate the actual corner width. Both corners added will never be more than the height. The result would be corner_radius_top_left: 10 and corner_radius_bottom_left: 20.
---CHUNK---
