Document: StyleBoxFlat
Path: godot/classes/class_styleboxflat.rst
Summary: This section details properties of StyleBoxFlat related to antialiasing, background and border colors, border widths, and corner radii.

Properties:
anti_aliasing (bool): Default: true. Antialiasing draws a small ring around the edges, which fades to transparency. As a result, edges look much smoother. This is only noticeable when using rounded corners or skew. Note: When using beveled corners with 45-degree angles (corner_detail = 1), it is recommended to set anti_aliasing to false to ensure crisp visuals and avoid possible visual glitches.
Method: set_anti_aliased(value: bool)
Method: is_anti_aliased()

anti_aliasing_size (float): Default: 1.0. This changes the size of the antialiasing effect. 1.0 is recommended for an optimal result at 100% scale, identical to how rounded rectangles are rendered in web browsers and most vector drawing software. Note: Higher values may produce a blur effect but can also create undesired artifacts on small boxes with large-radius corners.
Method: set_aa_size(value: float)
Method: get_aa_size()

bg_color (Color): Default: Color(0.6, 0.6, 0.6, 1). The background color of the stylebox.
Method: set_bg_color(value: Color)
Method: get_bg_color()

border_blend (bool): Default: false. If true, the border will fade into the background color.
Method: set_border_blend(value: bool)
Method: get_border_blend()

border_color (Color): Default: Color(0.8, 0.8, 0.8, 1). Sets the color of the border.
Method: set_border_color(value: Color)
Method: get_border_color()

border_width_bottom (int): Default: 0. Border width for the bottom border.
Method: set_border_width(margin: Side, width: int)
Method: get_border_width(margin: Side) const

border_width_left (int): Default: 0. Border width for the left border.
Method: set_border_width(margin: Side, width: int)
Method: get_border_width(margin: Side) const

border_width_right (int): Default: 0. Border width for the right border.
Method: set_border_width(margin: Side, width: int)
Method: get_border_width(margin: Side) const

border_width_top (int): Default: 0. Border width for the top border.
Method: set_border_width(margin: Side, width: int)
Method: get_border_width(margin: Side) const

corner_detail (int): Default: 8. This sets the number of vertices used for each corner. Higher values result in rounder corners but take more processing power to compute. When choosing a value, you should take the corner radius (set_corner_radius_all()) into account. For corner radii less than 10, 4 or 5 should be enough. For corner radii less than 30, values between 8 and 12 should be enough. A corner detail of 1 will result in chamfered corners instead of rounded corners, which is useful for some artistic effects.
Method: set_corner_detail(value: int)
Method: get_corner_detail()

corner_radius_bottom_left (int): Default: 0. The bottom-left corner's radius. If 0, the corner is not rounded.
Method: set_corner_radius(corner: Corner, radius: int)
Method: get_corner_radius(corner: Corner) const

corner_radius_bottom_right (int): Default: 0. The bottom-right corner's radius. If 0, the corner is not rounded.
Method: set_corner_radius(corner: Corner, radius: int)
Method: get_corner_radius(corner: Corner) const

corner_radius_top_left (int): Default: 0. The top-left corner's radius. If 0, the corner is not rounded.
Method: set_corner_radius(corner: Corner, radius: int)
Method: get_corner_radius(corner: Corner) const

corner_radius_top_right (int): Default: 0. The top-right corner's radius. If 0, the corner is not rounded.
Method: set_corner_radius(corner: Corner, radius: int)
Method: get_corner_radius(corner: Corner) const
